<p>Most engineers assume that dropping a VPN or a Kubernetes CNI into their stack is enough to secure agent-to-agent communication. It is not. Autonomous AI agents operate across clouds, spawn dynamically, and need persistent, verifiable identities that traditional overlays were never designed to provide. The gap between legacy networking and what modern agentic systems actually require is wider than most teams realize. This article breaks down overlay networking fundamentals, compares the leading technologies, and gives you a practical framework for building secure, scalable overlays for AI automation in 2026.</p>
